00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:03.870
That's a huge group and
they need the same things,

221
00:12:03.870 --> 00:12:06.960
observability,
governance, security.

222
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:08.520
SUNIL GARG: Yeah,
absolutely correct.

223
00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:13.890
So that's exactly where
Agent 365 SDK comes in.

224
00:12:13.890 --> 00:12:17.400
This will be a long answer, but
let's quickly talk through this.

225
00:12:17.400 --> 00:12:21.990
So the first thing I would say
is Agent 365 SDK is not all

226
00:12:21.990 --> 00:12:23.790
or nothing.

227
00:12:23.790 --> 00:12:27.810
Whether you are building with
OpenAI's SDK, LangChain, Claude,

228
00:12:27.810 --> 00:12:32.880
LlamaIndex, the Microsoft Agent
Framework or fully custom code,

229
00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:35.880
you can layer Agent
365 capabilities

230
00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:40.710
onto what you are already
running incrementally.

231
00:12:40.710 --> 00:12:44.910
You pick where to start and
how far you want to go,

232
00:12:44.910 --> 00:12:49.290
which are observability,
governance, and security.

233
00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:51.840
Now, let's start
with observability.

234
00:12:51.840 --> 00:12:56.730
The SDK adds full open
telemetry-based tracing,

235
00:12:56.730 --> 00:13:00.600
which means every input, every
output, every tool call,

236
00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:03.030
every model invocation.

237
00:13:03.030 --> 00:13:05.940
Developers have two
paths from here.

238
00:13:05.940 --> 00:13:09.360
The first, and the one
what we recommend,

239
00:13:09.360 --> 00:13:12.480
is the Microsoft
OpenTelemetry Distro.

240
00:13:12.480 --> 00:13:15.450
It comes with auto
instrumentation for OpenAI,

241
00:13:15.450 --> 00:13:17.820
and LangChain, and
Agent Framework,

242
00:13:17.820 --> 00:13:20.760
plus hooks for everything else.

243
00:13:20.760 --> 00:13:25.680
The second path is direct
injection to an OTel endpoint.

244
00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:30.930
So let's say you already have an
open telemetry pipeline running

245
00:13:30.930 --> 00:13:35.370
or you are on a stack that
our SDK does not support yet,

246
00:13:35.370 --> 00:13:37.800
